summary: An ordinance appropriating the sum of $40.00 out of the General Fund of the City of Seattle, to pay the claim of R. O. Fritch for injuries to a buck skin horse weighing about 1000 pounds, received by said horse on the 13th day of December 1915, at about 4:00 P.M., on the south side of Jackson Street, between Maynard Avenue and 7th Avenue South, in said city, and authorizing the drawing of a warrant therefor.
